# Supabase Auth — Sessions, Tokens & SSR Reference

> This file explains HOW Supabase auth actually works under the hood.
> Understanding this prevents the most common auth bugs in Rocket projects.

---

## JWT Signing Algorithm — New Default Since May 2025

```
Projects created after May 1, 2025: default is RS256 (asymmetric — public/private key pair)
Projects created before May 2025: default is HS256 (symmetric — shared secret)

Check your project: Dashboard → Auth → JWT → Signing Algorithm

Impact on your code:
  supabase-js: no change — works the same
  Third-party JWT verification: HS256 uses your JWT secret; RS256 uses a public key URL
  OAuth 2.1 server: requires RS256 — new projects already have this

Third-party JWT verification with RS256:
  const JWKS_URL = 'https://[REF].supabase.co/auth/v1/jwks'
  // Fetch public key from JWKS_URL — do NOT hardcode the key
  // Use a library like jose: const { createRemoteJWKSet } = require('jose')
```

