## JWT Expiry vs Session Expiry — The Biggest Misconception

```
Dashboard → Auth → JWT expiry limit

This is NOT "how long until the user is logged out"
This is "how long the access token is valid before a silent refresh"

Sessions persist indefinitely via refresh tokens (unless you configure session controls)

Example:
  JWT expiry = 3600 (1 hour)
  User logs in Monday → access token expires Monday+1hr
  Supabase silently exchanges refresh token → new access token
  User is STILL logged in Tuesday, Wednesday, forever
  Until: they sign out, or their refresh token is revoked
```

